  91:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h **** 
  92:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h **** /**
  93:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * \ingroup clk_group
  94:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * \defgroup osc_group Oscillator Management
  95:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *
  96:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * This group contains functions and definitions related to configuring
  97:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * and enabling/disabling on-chip oscillators. Internal RC-oscillators,
  98:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * external crystal oscillators and external clock generators are
  99:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * supported by this module. What all of these have in common is that
 100:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * they swing at a fixed, nominal frequency which is normally not
 101:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * adjustable.
 102:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *
 103:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * \par Example: Enabling an oscillator
 104:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *
 105:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * The following example demonstrates how to enable the external
 106:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * oscillator on XMEGA A and wait for it to be ready to use. The
 107:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * oscillator identifiers are platform-specific, so while the same
 108:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * procedure is used on all platforms, the parameter to osc_enable()
 109:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * will be different from device to device.
 110:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * \code
 111:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h **** 	osc_enable(OSC_ID_XOSC);
 112:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h **** 	osc_wait_ready(OSC_ID_XOSC); \endcode
 113:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *
 114:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * \section osc_group_board Board-specific Definitions
 115:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * If external oscillators are used, the board code must provide the
 116:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * following definitions for each of those:
 117:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *   - \b BOARD_<osc name>_HZ: The nominal frequency of the oscillator.
 118:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *   - \b BOARD_<osc name>_STARTUP_US: The startup time of the
 119:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *     oscillator in microseconds.
 120:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *   - \b BOARD_<osc name>_TYPE: The type of oscillator connected, i.e.
 121:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *     whether it's a crystal or external clock, and sometimes what kind
 122:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *     of crystal it is. The meaning of this value is platform-specific.
 123:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  *
 124:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  * @{
 125:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h ****  */
 126:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h **** 
 127:.././hal//sam4s/inc/osc.h **** //! \name Oscillator Management
